# plans & module prompts — local only (owner decision 2026-07-10); the folder
# stays on disk and in editor search, it just never enters version control.
#
# `/docs/*` and not `/docs/`: git cannot re-include a file whose PARENT
# DIRECTORY is excluded — it never descends, so negations inside have no effect.
# Excluding the entries individually is what makes the four exceptions below
# possible. Those four are judge-facing by requirement (TS-15.7: "bounty
# writeups in /docs"); everything else — 22 module docs, 24 prompts, HANDOFF,
# notes/, references/, CONFLICTS, traceability, index — stays private.
# scripts/check-docs-tracked.mjs fails CI if that list ever grows by accident.
/docs/*
!/docs/writeup-ua-track.md
!/docs/writeup-arbitrum.md
!/docs/writeup-magic.md
!/docs/deployments.md

# root-level plans, specs, and prompt sources — local only, same decision as /docs/
/broker-agent-blueprint.md
/heirloom-blueprint.md
/retenix-blueprint.md
/retenix-claude-code-prompt.md
/retenix-design-system.md
/retenix-execution-prompts-generator.md
/retenix-product-spec.md
/retenix-technical-spec.md
/uxmaxx-hackathon-strategy.md

# foundry broadcast logs from local dry-runs (anvil chain 31337) — real-network
# broadcasts (421614/42161) stay committable as deploy records
contracts/broadcast/*/31337/
